tion disturbances and supraventricular arrhythmias." Am Heart J 78 (1969): 135-8[6] Markowitz JS, Wells BG, Carson WH "Interactions between antipsychotic and antihypertensive drugs." Ann Pharmacother 29 (1995): 603-9[7] "Product Information. Mellaril (thioridazine)." Sandoz Pharmaceuticals Corporation, East Hanover, NJ.[8] "Product Information. Prozac (fluoxetine)." Dista Products Company, Indianapolis, IN.[9] Silver JM, Yudofsky SC, Kogan M, Katz BL "Elevation of thioridazine plasma levels by propranolol." Am J Psychiatry 143 (1986): 1290-2[10] Hartigan-Go K, Bateman DN, Nyberg G, Martensson E, Thomas SHL "Concentration-related pharmacodynamic effects of thioridazine and its metabolites in humans." Clin Pharmacol Ther 60 (1996): 543-53[11] Greendyke RM, Kanter DR "Plasma propranolol levels and their effect on plasma thioridazine and haloperidol concentrations." J Clin Psychopharmacol 7 (1987): 178-82[12] Thomas M, Maconochie JG, Fletcher E "The dilemma of the prolonged QT interval in early drug studies." Br J Clin Pharmacol 41 (1996): 77-81[13] Cerner Multum, Inc. "Australian Product Information." O 0[14] Cerner Multum, Inc. "UK Summary of Product Characteristics." O 0[15] "Product Information. Gleevec (imatinib mesylate)." Novartis Pharmaceuticals, East Hanover, NJ.', 1767365206);
